        <strong>Anti-Inflammatory Powerhouse</strong>
        <p>Anthocyanins in Montmorency cherries inhibit COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes at concentrations comparable to ibuprofen (10mg level). A 2012 study showed 25-40% reduction in inflammatory markers CRP, IL-6, and TNF-alpha after just 21 days of daily tart cherry supplementation — without NSAID side effects.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="moon" size={22} /></div>
        <strong>Natural Melatonin Source</strong>
        <p>Tart cherries contain an average of 13.5ng of melatonin per gram — one of the highest natural food sources. A 2018 study found tart cherry juice increased sleep time by 84 minutes in adults with insomnia. The dual mechanism of direct melatonin plus enhanced tryptophan availability makes tart cherry uniquely effective for sleep.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="fitness" size={22} /></div>
